interfaces.label: FieldDefinition
description:
A {@link FieldDefinition} adapts a {@link UiSettingMetadata} object to be more
easily consumed by the UI.  It contains additional information about the field
that is determined from a given UiSettingMetadata object, (which is a type
representing a UiSetting).

children.label: ariaAttributes
description: UX ARIA attributes derived from the setting.

children.label: categories
description: A list of categories related to the field.

children.label: defaultValue
description: The default value of the field from Kibana.

children.label: defaultValueDisplay
description: The text-based display of the default value, for use in the UI.

children.label: deprecation
description: Deprecation information for the field

children.label: description
description: A description of the field.

children.label: displayName
description: The name of the field suitable for display in the UX.

children.label: groupId
description: The grouping identifier for the field.

children.label: id
description: The unique identifier of the field, typically separated by `:`

children.label: isCustom
description: True if the field is a custom setting, false otherwise.

children.label: isDefaultValue
description: True if the current saved setting matches the default setting.

children.label: isOverridden
description: True if the setting is overridden in Kibana, false otherwise.

children.label: isReadOnly
description: True if the setting is read-only, false otherwise.

children.label: metric
description: Metric information when one interacts with the field.
signature: { name?: string | undefined; type?: string | undefined; } | undefined

children.label: name
description: The name of the field suitable for use in the UX.

children.label: options
description: Option information if the field represents a `select` setting.
signature: { values: string[] | number[]; labels: Record<string, string>; } | undefined

children.label: order
description: A rank order for the field relative to other fields.

children.label: requiresPageReload
description: True if the browser must be reloaded for the setting to take effect, false otherwise.

children.label: savedValue
description: The current saved value of the setting.

children.label: type
description: The type of setting the field represents.

children.label: unsavedFieldId
description: An identifier of the field when it has an unsaved change.

interfaces.label: SelectFieldDefinition
description:
This is a {@link FieldDefinition} representing {@link UiSetting} `select` type
for use in the UI.

children.label: options
description: Options are required when this definition is used.
signature: { values: string[] | number[]; labels: Record<string, string>; }

interfaces.label: UiSettingMetadata
description:
This is an type-safe abstraction over the {@link UiSetting} type, whose fields
are not only optional, but also not strongly typed to
{@link @kbn/core-ui-settings-common#UiSettingsType}.

children.label: type
description: The type of setting being represented.

children.label: value
description: The default value in Kibana for the setting.

children.label: userValue
description: The value saved by the user.

interfaces.label: UnsavedFieldChange
description:
A {@link UnsavedFieldChange} represents local changes to a field that have not
yet been saved.

children.label: type
description: The type of setting.

children.label: error
description: An error message, if any, from the change.

children.label: isInvalid
description: True if the change is invalid for the field, false otherwise.

children.label: unsavedValue
description: The current unsaved value stored in the field.
